trans-unit.source:
You can continue to use R-Instat, however some functionality may be unavailable.
Possible Solutions:
1. If you selected "No" to the message boxes: "Would you like to use/create a Personal Library..." restart R-Instat and click "Yes" to both these messages to allow R-Instat to install R packages.
2. Ensure that R or RSudio are not running, as this can prevent R-Instat from installing packages. If they are, close them and restart R-Instat.
3. Restart and run R-Instat as an Administrator. Administrator priviledges are sometimes required to install R packages.
4. If you have an internet connect, click below to atempt to download and install the missing packages from an online server.
